# NIX FLAKE
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.nix
Source: https://github.com/NixOS/nix
Description: Manage Nix flakes (lock files, metadata, registry).
Version: nix --version

## Commands

### Basics
- nix flake init: Create a basic flake.nix in the current directory.
- nix flake check: Verify that the flake is valid and buildable.

### Essentials
- nix flake update: Update all inputs in flake.lock to their latest versions.
- nix flake lock --update-input nixpkgs: Update only a specific input.

### Intermediaries
- nix flake show: Display the outputs provided by the flake.
- nix flake metadata: Show information about the flake, including its inputs.

### Advanceds
- nix flake archive: Copy the flake and its inputs to the store.

### Uncommons
- nix flake clone <url>: Clone a flake's source repository.

## Tips
- Always check flake.lock into version control.

## Disclaimers
- Flakes are still technically an experimental feature.

## Alternatives
- nix-channel: Legacy way to manage package versions.

